reviewText: It was a heart warming story about family love loss and renewal it was nice of them to take that poor orphaned girl in and make her a part of their family.
Title: Swan Princess: A Royal Family Tale

reviewText: We enjoyed this princes classic with a family twist. It was rented for an 8 yr old who really liked it. The story was good and similar to other Swan Princess films where Odette is the main starlette. Nice moral lesson. Good lesson about the meaning of family.
Title: Swan Princess: A Royal Family Tale

reviewText: After Swan Princess Christmas I wasn't sure of the idea of another CGI  Swan Princess.  Once I started the movie I'm glad I bought it. Is as great as the original trilogy and a find addition to the Swan Prince legacy. The Dark Arts that been behind Odette's problems since the original film is back. Only this time instead of evil humans, the Dark Arts is attacking with an army of flying squirals who was tricked into believing The Swan Princess is evil.  When the Dark Arts itself kills a wood cutter Prince Derek and Princess Odette adopts his daughter who is kidnapped and must be rescued by a daring plan.
Title: Swan Princess: A Royal Family Tale

reviewText: This movie turned out to be pretty awesome. I'm a big fan of the Swan Princess series and I really love the new character Princess Alise.
summary: Good movie with a good moral lesson
Title: Swan Princess: A Royal Family Tale

reviewText: I felt drawn to seeing The Swan Princess: A Royal Family Tale after spotting it through the redbox machine of my Walmart gig (during one of my work breaks).The Swan Princess: A Royal Family Tale is an animated movie that involves Odette and her husband Derek unintentionally becoming involved in a matter that calls for them to save their kingdom. They also both unintentionally become parents  to a girl named Alise after she becomes orphaned.
Title: Swan Princess: A Royal Family Tale
